Author: joshuastover
Content: The black hole's gravity is so strong that we can see only a bright ring around it. The ring is the material, gas and dust, which the black hole is swallowing. The black hole is four million times the mass of our Sun. The ring around it is about 60 million kilometers, which is about the same as Mercury's orbit around the Sun. To take the image scientists used eight different telescopes around the world. They believe the image will help them understand gravity and how materials behave in the black hole.

Author: geoffnunan
Content: I've recently been looking at game development paradigms and their applicability to industry. I cam across the Entity Component System (ECS) paradigm. Has anyone explored using that for IIoT?

Author: sim_sam3
Content: I‚Äôve not related this to ECS although the comparison is fascinating, but I‚Äôve worked a bit with Zenoh‚Äôs peer features, and prototyped a lisp-style descriptive system with similar composition-based model (entity) creation. I have a public Zenoh Explorer (like Mqtt Explorer) app but haven‚Äôt plumbed in the same self-establishing modeling mesh; that‚Äôs still private. But glad to swap bits if you‚Äôre thinking of prototyping something like this on Z.

Author: geoffnunan
Content:
I have not been working with Zenoh, but have been playing with the specs crate to understand ECS pattern.
I did not like that only one instance of a component could be added to an entity, so have been refactoring specs to support hashmaps of component on an entity
